            {
              "id": "117adcea-afd1-31df-965c-c7eadffa5739",
              "name": "Detected Insecure Deserialization Vulnerability",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nInsecure deserialization is a vulnerability that occurs when untrusted data is deserialized by a program. This can lead to harmful consequences such as remote code execution, where an attacker can run arbitrary code on the victim's machine. In JavaScript, this vulnerability can occur when using functions like `eval()` or `Function()` to deserialize data.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, avoid deserializing data from untrusted sources. If deserialization is necessary, use safe alternatives like `JSON.parse()`. This function only parses JSON-formatted data, and does not evaluate the data as code.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is an example of a vulnerable code snippet and how to fix it:\n\n**Vulnerable Code:**\n\n```javascript\nvar user = eval('(' + req.body.user + ')');\n```\n\n**Fixed Code:**\n\n```javascript\nvar user = JSON.parse(req.body.user);\n```\n\nIn the fixed code, `JSON.parse()` is used instead of `eval()`. This prevents the server from evaluating potentially harmful code contained in `req.body.user`.\n\n## OWASP Resources\n\n- [OWASP Top 10 2017: A8-Insecure Deserialization](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/2017/A8_2017-Insecure_Deserialization)\n- [OWASP Cheat Sheet: Deserialization Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Deserialization_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n\n## Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)\n\n- [CWE-502: Deserialization of Untrusted Data](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/502.html)\n\nPlease note that all the links provided are active and accessible to anonymous users."
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-502",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/502.html"
