            {
              "id": "2643bd0e-c6cd-3e27-8fab-ffa486d4234d",
              "name": "\"XSS Vulnerability Risk in User-Controlled Data within `hoursSpan.innerHTML`\"",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe code snippet provided is vulnerable to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks. XSS is a type of injection security vulnerability where an attacker can inject malicious scripts into webpages viewed by other users. In this case, the vulnerability lies in the `hoursSpan.innerHTML` assignment. If the `t.hours` variable is user-controlled and not properly sanitized, an attacker could inject malicious scripts that would be executed when the `hoursSpan` element is rendered in the browser.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should always sanitize user-controlled data before using it in your code. This can be done by using output encoding libraries when outputting user-controlled data. Also, you should use contextual output encoding. For example, HTML encoding when injecting user-controlled data into HTML.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nInstead of using `innerHTML`, you can use `textContent` which does not parse HTML and therefore mitigates the risk of XSS attacks. Here is the fixed code:\n\n```javascript\nhoursSpan.textContent = ('0' + t.hours).slice(-2);\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code snippet provided does not appear to have any library dependencies.\n\n## OWASP Resources\n\n- [OWASP XSS (Cross Site Scripting) Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross_Site_Scripting_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [OWASP DOM based XSS Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/DOM_based_XSS_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n\n## Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)\n\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-79",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html"
