            {
              "id": "27ea7558-4421-3015-a697-2a35c477d23d",
              "name": "\"Vulnerability through Overriding Built-in Constructs\"",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\n\"Obfuscation by overriding built-in constructs\" is a vulnerability in JavaScript where an attacker manipulates or overrides built-in JavaScript constructs such as `Object`, `Array`, `Function`, etc. This can lead to unexpected behavior of the application, potentially leading to security risks such as code injection, data manipulation, or even remote code execution.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, developers should avoid using JavaScript's built-in constructs directly from user-controlled input. Instead, they should use safe APIs that do not evaluate code dynamically. \n\nDevelopers should also use JavaScript strict mode (`\"use strict\";`) which prevents certain actions from being taken and throws more exceptions.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nHere is an example of a vulnerable code and how to fix it:\n\n```javascript\n// Vulnerable code\nlet userControlledInput = getUserInput(); // Assume this function gets input from user\nlet obj = new Object(userControlledInput);\n\n// Fixed code\n\"use strict\";\nlet userControlledInput = getUserInput(); // Assume this function gets input from user\nlet obj = {};\nif (typeof userControlledInput === 'string') {\n    obj = userControlledInput;\n}\n```\n\nIn the fixed code, we are not directly passing user-controlled input to the `Object` constructor. Instead, we are checking if the input is a string and then assigning it to the object.\n\n## OWASP Resources\n\n- [OWASP Code Review Guide](https://owasp.org/www-pdf-archive/OWASP_Code_Review_Guide_v2.pdf)\n\n## Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)\n\n- [CWE-96: Improper Neutralization of Directives in Statically Saved Code ('Static Code Injection')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/96.html)\n- [CWE-95: Improper Neutralization of Directives in Dynamically Evaluated Code ('Eval Injection')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/95.html)\n\nPlease note that the links provided are active and accessible for anonymous users at the time of writing this report."
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-96",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/96.html"
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-95",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/95.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "CWE-96",
                  "CWE-95"
                ]
              }
