            {
              "id": "3fa07df3-fda7-3a5d-bdc3-4ef1459687c4",
              "name": "\"XSS Vulnerability Risk in User-Controlled Data in `hoursItem`\"",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe code snippet provided is vulnerable to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks. XSS is a type of injection security vulnerability where an attacker can inject malicious scripts into webpages viewed by other users. In this case, the vulnerability arises from the fact that the `hoursItem.innerHTML` is being set to a value that is derived from user-controlled data (`time.hours`). If an attacker can control the value of `time.hours`, they can inject malicious scripts that will be executed when the `hoursItem` is rendered on the webpage.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should always escape user-controlled data before rendering it on a webpage. This can be done using various methods depending on the context in which the data is used. In this case, since the data is being used in an HTML context, you should use a method that escapes HTML entities.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nA simple fix for this vulnerability would be to use `textContent` instead of `innerHTML`. The `textContent` property does not parse HTML, so any potential scripts that an attacker might inject will not be executed.\n\nHere is the fixed code:\n\n```javascript\nhoursItem.textContent = ('0' + time.hours).slice(-2);\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code snippet does not appear to have any library dependencies.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP XSS (Cross Site Scripting) Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross_Site_Scripting_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-79",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html"
