            {
              "id": "ab2e141d-a460-3ea3-a697-b7f124620cd0",
              "name": "XSS Vulnerability due to Dynamic Input in innerHTML",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nCross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerabilities occur when an application includes untrusted data in a new web page without proper validation or escaping, or updates an existing web page with user-supplied data using a browser API that can create HTML or JavaScript. XSS allows attackers to execute scripts in the victim's browser which can hijack user sessions, deface web sites, or redirect the user to malicious sites.\n\nIn this specific case, the vulnerability is due to the use of `innerHTML` property in JavaScript, which is used to get or set the HTML content of an element. If the content that is set via `innerHTML` includes user input, it can lead to an XSS vulnerability if the input is not properly sanitized.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should avoid using `innerHTML` with user-supplied input. Instead, use safer alternatives like `textContent` or `innerText` which do not interpret the passed content as HTML, but instead insert it as raw text.\n\nIf you must use `innerHTML`, make sure to properly sanitize the user input to remove any potentially harmful scripts. This can be done using a library that is specifically designed for this purpose, such as DOMPurify.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nReplace the vulnerable line of code with a safer alternative:\n\n```javascript\nminutesItem.textContent = ('0' + time.minutes).slice(-2);\n```\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example does not appear to have any library dependencies.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP XSS (Cross Site Scripting) Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross_Site_Scripting_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [OWASP DOM based XSS Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/DOM_based_XSS_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
