              "id": "ace59a22-3387-34e1-998a-2acbadd8360c",
              "name": "\"XSS Vulnerabilities from User-Controlled Data in 'MinutesSpan' Anti-Pattern\"",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe \"XSS Vulnerabilities from User-Controlled Data in 'MinutesSpan' Anti-Pattern\" vulnerability refers to a Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerability that occurs when user-controlled data is directly inserted into a web page without proper sanitization or validation. In this case, the vulnerability lies in the `minutesSpan.innerHTML` assignment, where `t.minutes` is user-controlled data.\n\nCross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks are a type of injection, in which malicious scripts are injected into otherwise benign and trusted websites. XSS attacks occur when an attacker uses a web application to send malicious code, generally in the form of a browser side script, to a different end user.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nTo mitigate this vulnerability, you should always escape untrusted HTTP request data based on the context in the HTML output (HTML body, HTML attribute, JavaScript, CSS, or URL) will be consumed. When the data is used in HTML body content, use HTML entity encoding. \n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nA simple fix for this specific vulnerability would be to sanitize the `t.minutes` input before inserting it into the `minutesSpan` element. This can be done using the `textContent` property instead of `innerHTML`:\n\n```javascript\nminutesSpan.textContent = ('0' + t.minutes).slice(-2);\n```\n\nThe `textContent` property does not interpret the passed content as HTML, but instead inserts it as raw text, which prevents any potential script from being executed.\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\nThe code example does not appear to have any specific library dependencies.\n\n## References\n\n- [OWASP XSS (Cross Site Scripting) Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross_Site_Scripting_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [OWASP DOM based XSS Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/DOM_based_XSS_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n- [CWE-79: Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/79.html)"
